Suspected assassins have killed the Majority Leader of Sapele Local Government Legislative Arm, Chief Venture Kagbude in Delta. The deceased who reportedly has two wives and children was killed at about 6:00 p.m on Tuesday. He was reportedly returning from Okuoke community along the Sapele-Effurun/Warri road where he had gone to inspect a building project he was putting up for his mother. The gunmen were said to have laid an ambush for the lawmaker and shot him dead. Zulum approves N26m for Borno students in Saudi Land border will remain closed ― Ali tells NASS Don, others bag awards at MGS 40th anniversary Minimum wage: We can’t guarantee industrial peace… ALSO READ: BREAKING: Tribunal affirms Ganduje as duly elected Kano governor, dismisses PDP’s petition Chief Kagbude was until his death the chairman of Okirighre Community in Sapele LGA as well as the chairman of Host Communities (HOSTCOM) in the local government. The lawmaker is believed to be one of the persons discouraging activities of ritual killings, cultist as well as other criminal activities in the area. Sources from Sapele LGA told Tribune Online that the council’s authorities had already visited the deceased’s family and vowed to apprehend the killers. Although a police source who spoke to Tribune Online confirmed the killing, Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Onome Onovwakpoyeya when contacted, however, promised to confirm the incident and call back. How premature ejaculation  and small penis almost ruin my marriage and made my wife cheat on me, until my Abuja doctor recommend this powerful but simple solution that work wonder...DONT BE A VICTIM.... SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
